      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a classic example of how government regulation directly pressures small businesses. Increased labor costs force owners to either raise prices, which can hurt customer volume, or cut back on staff and services. This ultimately squeezes the profit margins of local establishments, making expansion plans much riskier. Businesses need to run a tight operation, and sudden wage increases are a direct threat to that stability.",
      "source": "target",
